From ae2ccd34554ce77f4c40785ba524e949fef357b5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex Figueiredo <alex.fernandesfigueiredo@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Feb 2026 17:37:54 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] keep app.kubernetes.io/name label always enabled

Since [1], stx-openstack Charts have been deployed including
the `app.kubernetes.io/name` label by default. However, the
Openstack-Helm (OSH) community has also included the additional labels
`app.kubernetes.io/component` and `app.kubernetes.io/instance` [2].

The addtional labels added by OSH community and brought to
stx-openstack during Epoxy upgrade broke the helm charts backward
compatibility, blocking stx-openstack upgrades between Caracal and
Epoxy based versions. This issue was also noticed by the OSH community
and a new config `pod.labels.include_app_kubernetes_io` was included to
disable the new labels when required [3].

To enable backward compatibility with stx-openstack Caracal based
versions, this patch keep `app.kubernetes.io/name` label always
enabled and allow the user to disable the incompatible OSH labels
per Helm Chart by setting `pod.labels.include_app_kubernetes_io: false`.

[1]https://review.opendev.org/c/starlingx/openstack-armada-app/+/930508
[2]https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-helm-infra/+/930948
[3]https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/openstack-helm/+/946090

Signed-off-by: Alex Figueiredo <alex.fernandesfigueiredo@windriver.com>
---
 helm-toolkit/templates/snippets/_kubernetes_metadata_labels.tpl | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/helm-toolkit/templates/snippets/_kubernetes_metadata_labels.tpl b/helm-toolkit/templates/snippets/_kubernetes_metadata_labels.tpl
index 5439a812e..2ece8f7e0 100644
--- a/helm-toolkit/templates/snippets/_kubernetes_metadata_labels.tpl
+++ b/helm-toolkit/templates/snippets/_kubernetes_metadata_labels.tpl
@@ -42,8 +42,8 @@ return: |
 release_group: {{ $envAll.Values.release_group | default $envAll.Release.Name }}
 application: {{ $application }}
 component: {{ $component }}
-{{- if or $labels.include_app_kubernetes_io (not (hasKey $labels "include_app_kubernetes_io")) }}
 app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ $application }}
+{{- if or $labels.include_app_kubernetes_io (not (hasKey $labels "include_app_kubernetes_io")) }}
 app.kubernetes.io/component: {{ $component }}
 app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ $envAll.Values.release_group | default $envAll.Release.Name }}
 {{- end -}}
-- 
